net.hudup.core.data

Interface Profiles

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.io.Serializable, Transfer
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MemProfiles

    public interface Profiles
extends Cloneable, Transfer, java.io.Serializable
    This interface represents a collection of profiles. Recall that each profile is represented by Profile class. As a convention, this interface is called profiles or table or profile list. This interface provides methods to retrieve profile (s) and additional information. Any class that implements this interface needs to have a built-in variable containing Profile (s). Note that Profile is one of important data structures, like record of table in database, has a list of values. Each value belongs to a particular attribute. Profile uses attributes to specify its data types.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen
